      <bioghist id="aspace_adcda1178d807c37831c802ecec54953">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <chronlist>
      
            <chronitem>
               <datesingle>1798 Jan 24</datesingle>
               <chronitemset>
                  <event>Born, lived in Wilbraham, Massachusetts</event>
               </chronitemset>
            </chronitem>
            <chronitem>
               <datesingle>1822</datesingle>
               <chronitemset>
                  <event>Conducted evangelistic ministry--largely in New Jersey, Westchester and Suffolk Counties, New York, and Greenwich area of Connecticut</event>
                  <event>Licensed and ordained for work as an evangelist</event>
                  <event>Studied for the ministry under Alfred Ely</event>
                  <event>Attended Union College</event>
               </chronitemset>
            </chronitem>
            <chronitem>
               <datesingle>ca. 1834</datesingle>
               <chronitemset>
                  <event>Died</event>
               </chronitemset>
            </chronitem>
         </chronlist>
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_7e6e73b08ff08e1abcdc5f46fdfdafe5">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>These papers shed light on the training, life, and work of Noah C. Saxton, an early nineteenth century evangelist in America. A detailed summary of the collection prepared by Constance R. Spande is available in folder 17.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
